WEBVTT

1
00:02:30.942 --> 00:02:32.317
The Golden Tooth

2
00:02:32.318 --> 00:02:34.988
is honored to receive you.
my Lord Lannister.

3
00:02:34.989 --> 00:02:39.324
I have 500
fighting men. armed

4
00:02:39.325 --> 00:02:42.412
- and full of spirit.
- I bring a thousand knights of my own.

5
00:02:42.413 --> 00:02:45.602
and seven times as many archers
and men-at-arms.

6
00:02:45.603 --> 00:02:48.793
By the time we are finished
with the Riverland scum.

7
00:02:48.794 --> 00:02:51.296
the Red Fork
will have earned its name.

8
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:55.759
We are ready to march
at your command. my lord.

9
00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:59.261
I suppose you will make
for Harrenhal at once.

10
00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:02.015
I want you to send
a raven to King's Landing.

11
00:03:02.724 --> 00:03:05.976
Tell my brother
we are ready to march

12
00:03:05.977 --> 00:03:09.814
as soon as Prince Aemond
is able to join us...

13
00:03:09.815 --> 00:03:11.316
on Vhagar.

14
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:16.529
And until the prince
makes his answer. my lord?

15
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:18.822
My men have had
a long march.

16
00:03:18.823 --> 00:03:21.326
They are most eager
to embrace the hospitality

17
00:03:21.327 --> 00:03:24.496
of your keep.

18
00:03:37.092 --> 00:03:40.095
He dares to summon me!

19
00:03:40.845 --> 00:03:42.681
"With haste"?

20
00:03:43.264 --> 00:03:45.183
Are the Lannisters so diminished that
they cannot march

21
00:03:45.184 --> 00:03:47.686
from the Tooth to Harrenhal
without an escort?

22
00:03:49.854 --> 00:03:52.648
There is a large dragon in the Riverlands.
Your Grace.

23
00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:55.985
- My brother's army is strong. but it does seem...
- I am the prince regent.

24
00:03:55.986 --> 00:03:58.737
not a dog to be
called to heel.

25
00:03:58.738 --> 00:04:01.032
Tell your brother
that if he does not deliver his host

26
00:04:01.033 --> 00:04:03.325
to Harrenhal.
"with haste."

27
00:04:03.326 --> 00:04:05.870
Daemon's dragon will become
the least of his worries.

28
00:04:05.871 --> 00:04:07.746
Your irritations are
justified. Aemond.

29
00:04:07.747 --> 00:04:09.708
- but it does seem...
- I have a task for you

30
00:04:09.709 --> 00:04:12.210
as well.
Ser Tyland.

31
00:04:18.299 --> 00:04:20.427
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

32
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.221
I've had enough
of this cursed blockade.

33
00:04:24.222 --> 00:04:28.351
My prince... you cannot mean to treat
with the Free Cities.

34
00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:31.228
The captains of their ships
are dangerous mercenaries.

35
00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:33.398
- little more than pirates...
- They are a stone's throw away

36
00:04:33.399 --> 00:04:35.066
across the Narrow Sea.

37
00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:38.862
Lannister and Hightower ships
will take months to arrive.

38
00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:44.034
The Triarchy will delight in the chance
to terrorize the Sea Snake again.

39
00:04:44.035 --> 00:04:46.368
Let them weaken
his blockade

40
00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:49.247
while our true allies make
their long journey east.

41
00:04:49.956 --> 00:04:52.542
The Triarchy may play
at accepting terms.

42
00:04:52.543 --> 00:04:53.877
but they are not
to be trusted.

43
00:04:53.878 --> 00:04:56.628
Your father
knew this.

44
00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:58.298
What has come
of our letters to the Greyjoys?

45
00:04:58.299 --> 00:05:00.592
They have been
to no avail.

46
00:05:00.593 --> 00:05:02.760
The Red Kraken waits.

47
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.428
seeking his
best advantage.

48
00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:08.266
Though we may draw him in with honey.
if it comes to it.

49
00:05:08.267 --> 00:05:09.726
An offer of marriage.
perhaps.

50
00:05:09.727 --> 00:05:11.102
to the dowager queen?

51
00:05:11.936 --> 00:05:13.605
Out of the question.

52
00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:16.732
Alas.

53
00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:19.778
The dowager queen
speaks wisely. Your Grace.

54
00:05:19.779 --> 00:05:21.278
Even if the blockade
could be broken.

55
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.740
are we to invite
these alien raiders into our waters.

56
00:05:23.741 --> 00:05:25.908
so close
to King's Landing?

57
00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:28.953
It's time you set out
for Harrenhal. I think.

58
00:05:31.539 --> 00:05:33.666
Your Grace.
if Daemon prevails in the Riverlands.

59
00:05:33.667 --> 00:05:35.794
I no longer
have the numbers to challenge him.

60
00:05:37.504 --> 00:05:39.172
We lost much
at Rook's Rest.

61
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:40.965
as you well know.

62
00:05:43.677 --> 00:05:47.597
The longer we wait.
the more chance he will prevail.

63
00:05:47.598 --> 00:05:50.140
Lannister will march
from the west.

64
00:05:50.141 --> 00:05:52.184
Take what strength we have
and force Daemon

65
00:05:52.185 --> 00:05:55.605
- and his Riverlords to fight on two fronts.
- His Grace speaks wisely.

66
00:05:55.606 --> 00:05:57.774
We would do better to await
the Hightower host

67
00:05:57.775 --> 00:05:59.984
- and set out in good time.
- There is no time.

68
00:05:59.985 --> 00:06:01.986
It's a fortnight's
march to Harrenhal.

69
00:06:01.987 --> 00:06:03.988
We must strike before
his army is raised.

70
00:06:03.989 --> 00:06:06.323
And you yourself?

71
00:06:06.324 --> 00:06:08.993
I will fly out to meet you
when the time is ripe.

72
00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.330
My uncle is
a challenge I welcome...

73
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:14.791
if he dares face me.

74
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:21.256
I see we're all agreed.

75
00:06:26.845 --> 00:06:28.096
Your Grace.

76
00:06:33.060 --> 00:06:34.561
Mother...

77
00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.522
a word.

78
00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:46.363
I caution you.
Aemond.

79
00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:48.658
- boldness is one thing. but overconfidence...
- Remind me of your place

80
00:06:48.659 --> 00:06:50.535
on the small council.

81
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:53.746
You know very well
I represented

82
00:06:53.747 --> 00:06:55.330
your father during
the last years of his life.

83
00:06:55.331 --> 00:06:58.460
- and I have been a councilor to Aegon.
- Capably so.

84
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:01.046
My father's dead

85
00:07:01.796 --> 00:07:03.214
and Aegon is...

86
00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:05.884
Mm.

87
00:07:09.637 --> 00:07:11.431
You served
the realm well...

88
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:14.059
at a time of need.

89
00:07:15.894 --> 00:07:19.064
That need is ended.
You are no longer obliged.

90
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:21.357
It's not a matter
of obligation.

91
00:07:21.358 --> 00:07:22.775
This council has need
of a tempering voice.

92
00:07:22.776 --> 00:07:24.778
We have more than enough of those.
if you ask me.

93
00:07:24.779 --> 00:07:27.364
You have
the impetuousness of youth...

94
00:07:27.365 --> 00:07:28.530
and its arrogance.

95
00:07:28.531 --> 00:07:29.741
neither of which
is to be desired in a king.

96
00:07:29.742 --> 00:07:31.368
I release you
of your seat.

97
00:07:31.369 --> 00:07:32.827
such as it was.

98
00:07:33.578 --> 00:07:36.247
I'm sure you'll be
much pleased to return to more...

99
00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:39.125
domestic pursuits.

100
00:07:50.804 --> 00:07:52.409
Have the indignities
of your childhood

101
00:07:52.410 --> 00:07:54.015
not yet sufficiently
been avenged?

102
00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.452
You have
the gratitude of the crown.

103
00:09:13.428 --> 00:09:15.013
Your Grace.

104
00:09:20.894 --> 00:09:22.687
Bring him forth.

105
00:09:34.532 --> 00:09:36.951
Ser Steffon Darklyn.
Your Grace.

106
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:42.040
Is aught amiss.
Your Grace?

107
00:09:42.540 --> 00:09:43.666
My lords.

108
00:09:43.667 --> 00:09:46.043
I find myself.
Ser Steffon.

109
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.421
in an impossible
position.

110
00:09:49.631 --> 00:09:52.092
I have lost
Princess Rhaenys

111
00:09:52.093 --> 00:09:53.676
and her dragon.

112
00:09:53.677 --> 00:09:56.783
I hold an island seat
with no land army.

113
00:09:56.784 --> 00:09:59.891
And I must not go
to battle myself...

114
00:09:59.892 --> 00:10:01.100
as I am constantly told.

115
00:10:01.101 --> 00:10:03.435
lest I am slain
or captured.

116
00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:06.731
and... with me.
our hopes of victory.

117
00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:12.570
There is still Daemon and Caraxes...
and the Rivermen.

118
00:10:13.571 --> 00:10:15.407
That remains
to be seen.

119
00:10:17.575 --> 00:10:21.746
In any case. I must now proceed
as if I stand alone.

120
00:10:22.914 --> 00:10:24.708
And I see now.
that to do that.

121
00:10:24.709 --> 00:10:26.709
I need more
dragonriders

122
00:10:26.710 --> 00:10:30.088
for Vermithor and Silverwing.
and for Seasmoke.

123
00:10:30.089 --> 00:10:32.464
who I believe
misses his bond.

124
00:10:32.465 --> 00:10:36.260
But there are no more
in your family. Your Grace.

125
00:10:36.261 --> 00:10:38.930
- Your younger sons are babes.
- Mm.

126
00:10:40.265 --> 00:10:42.267
Mm. there is
Princess Rhaena.

127
00:10:42.767 --> 00:10:45.769
She has
attempted it. alas.

128
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:48.982
but the dragons here
would not take her as a rider.

129
00:10:48.983 --> 00:10:51.109
- Then who could do it?
- You.

130
00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:57.281
You are
of noble birth.

131
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:59.450
And I had always heard.
as you know.

132
00:10:59.451 --> 00:11:03.788
that the Darklyns and the Targaryens
had some common blood.

133
00:11:03.789 --> 00:11:07.500
I looked into the history.
and indeed it is true.

134
00:11:07.501 --> 00:11:10.169
Your grandmother's
grandmother. Aeriana.

135
00:11:10.170 --> 00:11:12.505
was born a Targaryen princess.

136
00:11:12.506 --> 00:11:14.799
And I have been
thinking.

137
00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:16.676
could it be possible?

138
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:19.324
To even consider
such a thing.

139
00:11:19.325 --> 00:11:21.430
I must protest.
Your Grace.

140
00:11:21.431 --> 00:11:23.975
the risk involved
in such a venture...

141
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:27.811
I am but a man.

142
00:11:27.812 --> 00:11:30.856
The dragons
are gods.

143
00:11:30.857 --> 00:11:34.402
Your Grace honors me
beyond what I deserve.

144
00:11:39.491 --> 00:11:44.162
You understand your peril.
Ser Steffon?

145
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:46.706
I do not compel you
to do this.

146
00:11:47.374 --> 00:11:50.709
It has never been
attempted before.

147
00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:54.839
To claim a dragon.
you must also be prepared to die.

148
00:11:55.423 --> 00:11:58.468
I well understand the risk
and I accept it with gladness.

149
00:11:58.469 --> 00:12:01.513
{\an8}I swore to ward
my queen with all my strength.

150
00:12:01.514 --> 00:12:03.181
{\an8}and to give
my blood for hers.

151
00:12:04.432 --> 00:12:06.434
That is my oath.
Your Grace.

152
00:12:08.687 --> 00:12:10.897
Then perhaps
the gods will favor us.

153
00:12:40.719 --> 00:12:42.137
Brother?

154
00:12:53.565 --> 00:12:55.775
Did you say it?

155
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:59.571
"The Heir for a Day."

156
00:13:00.447 --> 00:13:02.239
Did you say it?

157
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:06.077
You can't possibly
still be angry about this.

158
00:13:06.078 --> 00:13:09.748
My family was
just destroyed.

159
00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:12.917
You should've
been at my side.

160
00:13:14.586 --> 00:13:17.589
But instead you chose to celebrate
your own rise.

161
00:13:17.590 --> 00:13:19.298
Laughing at me...

162
00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:22.719
laughing with the whores
and lickspittles.

163
00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:24.553
No.

164
00:13:24.554 --> 00:13:26.598
You have no allies
at court but me.

165
00:13:27.599 --> 00:13:29.559
I have only ever
defended you.

166
00:13:29.976 --> 00:13:33.146
And everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face!

167
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:39.611
- I have decided...
- Don't.

168
00:13:39.612 --> 00:13:41.945
...to name
a new heir.

169
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.365
You are to return
to Runestone

170
00:13:44.366 --> 00:13:46.784
and your lady wife
at once.

171
00:13:46.785 --> 00:13:50.288
and you are to do so
without quarrel.

172
00:13:50.289 --> 00:13:53.333
by order of your king.

173
00:14:16.461 --> 00:14:18.400
No!

174
00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:23.154
Open the door!

175
00:14:36.084 --> 00:14:38.712
Open the door. Please.

176
00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.090
Please.

177
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:45.968
Please. Ah!

178
00:14:51.099 --> 00:14:53.351
May I be of assistance.
Your Grace?

179
00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:57.480
- What are you playing at. old man?
- I do wonder. Your Grace.

180
00:14:57.481 --> 00:14:58.897
if you're getting
enough sleep.

181
00:14:58.898 --> 00:15:01.067
- This old place...
- Are you mocking me?

182
00:15:01.068 --> 00:15:02.736
- No.
- Sit!

183
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:08.491
Or are you perhaps the culprit
who has been tampering with my peace?

184
00:15:08.492 --> 00:15:10.535
A friend by day
and a foe by night.

185
00:15:11.453 --> 00:15:13.163
- To what end?
- To mine. perhaps.

186
00:15:13.164 --> 00:15:14.205
Ah!

187
00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:20.962
Perhaps...
you resent my being here.

188
00:15:22.380 --> 00:15:23.798
Perhaps...

189
00:15:25.050 --> 00:15:27.051
you are an agent

190
00:15:27.052 --> 00:15:30.347
of the Hightower rabble.

191
00:15:30.348 --> 00:15:32.286
Ha. Or are you
still in league

192
00:15:32.287 --> 00:15:34.224
with your
club-footed nephew?

193
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:37.437
- Or is it Rhaenyra herself?!
- I assure you...

194
00:15:37.438 --> 00:15:39.397
I assure you.
Your Grace.

195
00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:54.371
Whatever your game is.
Strong...

196
00:15:54.372 --> 00:15:56.414
I assure you...

197
00:15:57.082 --> 00:16:00.502
- your king is on his guard.
- Yes. Your Grace.

198
00:16:04.798 --> 00:16:06.800
And stop
watching me.

199
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:43.336
You weren't going
to bid me farewell?

200
00:16:43.337 --> 00:16:45.796
There's something
wrong with me.

201
00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:49.634
Someone poisoned me.
The food. the wine.

202
00:16:49.635 --> 00:16:51.094
Or else it's this
swamp air. or...

203
00:16:51.095 --> 00:16:52.678
The ghost
of Harren the Black

204
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:54.848
moaning his curses
from Kingspyre Tower.

205
00:16:54.849 --> 00:16:56.807
Drivel!
All of it!

206
00:16:56.808 --> 00:16:59.476
The ghosts. the curses.
the blasted weirwood bed!

207
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:02.814
- I'm done with it!
- Ah. yes. It is your way. is it not?

208
00:17:02.815 --> 00:17:05.108
When something does not please you.
you run.

209
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.652
Dragonstone.
the Stepstones.

210
00:17:07.653 --> 00:17:09.153
Pentos. Harrenhal.

211
00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:11.156
I awake and I do not
know where I've been.

212
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:15.430
There are older things
in this world

213
00:17:15.431 --> 00:17:18.663
than you or I.
or living memory.

214
00:17:20.331 --> 00:17:24.377
You are not the player.
but a piece on the board.

215
00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:27.505
As am I.
for that matter.

216
00:17:29.716 --> 00:17:31.175
I'm not like you.

217
00:17:31.176 --> 00:17:34.429
In some ways. no.

218
00:17:35.013 --> 00:17:37.682
You struggle to see
there's an anger that blinds you.

219
00:17:37.683 --> 00:17:39.893
She never even wanted it.

220
00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:43.187
The crown.
She spared it no thought.

221
00:17:43.188 --> 00:17:45.690
Well. that's perhaps
why your brother gave the crown to her.

222
00:17:45.691 --> 00:17:47.358
Perhaps those
who strive for it

223
00:17:47.359 --> 00:17:49.027
are the least
suited to wear it.

224
00:17:49.028 --> 00:17:50.904
Don't lecture me!

225
00:17:56.576 --> 00:17:59.871
Viserys never wanted it himself.
if you recall.

226
00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:04.041
It came to him.
and he did his best.

227
00:18:04.042 --> 00:18:07.837
It's not a prize to be won.
but a burden to bear.

228
00:18:25.105 --> 00:18:27.232
If you have any counsel for dealing
with the Riverlords.

229
00:18:27.233 --> 00:18:29.067
I'd be glad of it.

230
00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:37.033
Daemon Targaryen
asking for help?

231
00:18:37.034 --> 00:18:38.243
Counsel.

232
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:46.418
House Tully is not the largest house
in the Riverlands.

233
00:18:46.419 --> 00:18:47.961
nor is it
the richest.

234
00:18:47.962 --> 00:18:49.504
but it is
the most stable.

235
00:18:50.422 --> 00:18:51.755
The Tullys'
wisdom has kept

236
00:18:51.756 --> 00:18:53.778
the river houses
in line for centuries.

237
00:18:53.779 --> 00:18:55.801
They would kill each other
to the last man

238
00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:58.096
if it were not for their liege lord.

239
00:18:58.972 --> 00:19:01.433
That dotard is
of no use to us.

240
00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:05.979
But Grover Tully is
their Lord Paramount.

241
00:19:06.604 --> 00:19:09.983
Without him.
they will never raise their banners as one.

242
00:19:09.984 --> 00:19:11.568
Rivermen are
made of mud.

243
00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:13.611
They would rather
die stuck in it

244
00:19:13.612 --> 00:19:15.113
than yield one inch
to one another.

245
00:19:15.114 --> 00:19:16.781
Then I can
do nothing.

246
00:19:16.782 --> 00:19:19.617
You... no.

247
00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:30.170
I need help. Alys.

248
00:19:32.839 --> 00:19:34.466
Do nothing now.

249
00:19:36.051 --> 00:19:38.845
In three days' time.
the winds will shift.

250
00:21:31.833 --> 00:21:32.834
Gods.

251
00:21:42.969 --> 00:21:44.596
Seasmoke...

252
00:21:46.514 --> 00:21:47.723
<i>Dohaeras.</i>

253
00:21:58.151 --> 00:22:00.195
Do not show fear.

254
00:22:01.279 --> 00:22:02.614
<i>Rybas!</i>

255
00:23:18.857 --> 00:23:20.233
I've done it.

256
00:23:27.699 --> 00:23:29.700
{\an8}No.

257
00:23:49.888 --> 00:23:51.493
Mother!

258
00:23:57.228 --> 00:24:00.357
{\an8}Up. up. up!

259
00:24:03.401 --> 00:24:05.152
Alyn!

260
00:24:05.153 --> 00:24:06.905
M'lord.

261
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:10.450
I'm pleased
with our progress.

262
00:24:10.909 --> 00:24:13.328
This ship will sail
in a few days' time.

263
00:24:14.079 --> 00:24:15.538
The blockade
is sure to be challenged.

264
00:24:15.539 --> 00:24:17.081
be it by Lions
or Krakens.

265
00:24:17.082 --> 00:24:19.876
Your men will be
glad to have you among 'em.

266
00:24:19.877 --> 00:24:21.419
I wish you
to sail with me.

267
00:24:22.671 --> 00:24:25.130
As my first mate.

268
00:24:25.131 --> 00:24:27.424
I'm grateful for the offer.
m'lord...

269
00:24:27.425 --> 00:24:29.218
- but...
- We will set course for Sharp Point.

270
00:24:29.219 --> 00:24:32.972
Lord Bar Emmon wishes to send
his nephew aboard as a boatswain.

271
00:24:32.973 --> 00:24:35.642
There are more experienced men
at your service.

272
00:24:37.435 --> 00:24:39.311
I was younger
than you

273
00:24:39.312 --> 00:24:41.398
when I took
my first command.

274
00:24:42.273 --> 00:24:44.609
You distinguished yourself
in the Stepstones.

275
00:24:44.610 --> 00:24:46.820
and you have
the respect of the crew.

276
00:24:48.363 --> 00:24:50.990
You are a fine choice
for this post.

277
00:24:53.993 --> 00:24:56.287
Is this an order
or a request?

278
00:24:58.456 --> 00:25:00.625
I will expect
you to report

279
00:25:00.626 --> 00:25:03.211
for your duties
on the morrow.

280
00:25:04.796 --> 00:25:06.464
As my lordship commands.

281
00:25:29.029 --> 00:25:31.156
- Bit thin. isn't it?
- It's either that or the fish.

282
00:25:31.157 --> 00:25:33.575
Nothing but fish
in this damn city.

283
00:25:36.536 --> 00:25:38.163
An ale here.

284
00:25:39.998 --> 00:25:41.832
Aught to eat with it?

285
00:25:41.833 --> 00:25:44.001
Don't think
I can stomach it. lass.

286
00:25:44.002 --> 00:25:46.671
Yeah. you've made the right choice there.
I'll tell you that.

287
00:25:49.341 --> 00:25:51.133
Makes you sick.
doesn't it?

288
00:25:51.134 --> 00:25:54.074
Knowing they're banqueting every night
at the castle.

289
00:25:54.075 --> 00:25:57.014
- while we go without.
- That can't be true.

290
00:25:57.015 --> 00:26:00.852
My girls were taken to
the Red Keep a few nights ago.

291
00:26:00.853 --> 00:26:04.251
Feasting and merriment
for the new Prince Regent.

292
00:26:04.252 --> 00:26:07.650
No! And him always
acting so correct.

293
00:26:07.651 --> 00:26:09.694
I'll tell you.
he's no penny pincher.

294
00:26:10.236 --> 00:26:14.074
- They were well-paid. and well-fed too.
- Hm.

295
00:26:14.075 --> 00:26:16.701
On what?
Fish with more fish on the side?

296
00:26:16.702 --> 00:26:19.537
Racks of lamb.
my love.

297
00:26:19.538 --> 00:26:22.374
Mince pies.
honey cakes.

298
00:26:22.375 --> 00:26:24.708
beef and gravy.

299
00:26:24.709 --> 00:26:26.210
And what do you think?

300
00:26:26.211 --> 00:26:29.714
There is to be another revel
on the morrow with dancing.

301
00:26:29.715 --> 00:26:31.132
That ain't right.

302
00:26:31.925 --> 00:26:33.927
Apologies.
my good man.

303
00:26:35.553 --> 00:26:37.471
I should not have
spoken so free.

304
00:26:37.472 --> 00:26:39.390
The royals would never
countenance me

305
00:26:39.391 --> 00:26:42.644
speaking about their bounty.
even if it's true.

306
00:26:43.728 --> 00:26:47.064
King Viserys loved his feasts
and his wine.

307
00:26:47.065 --> 00:26:50.402
but never while
our smallfolk went without.

308
00:26:50.403 --> 00:26:53.405
Mm. aye.
But he's gone now...

309
00:26:54.823 --> 00:26:57.784
and his rightful heir
denied her seat.

310
00:27:02.747 --> 00:27:06.751
Well... no use wondering
what might have been.

311
00:27:22.767 --> 00:27:24.748
...I am far from alone
among your councilors

312
00:27:24.749 --> 00:27:26.730
in holding this to be
a truly unfortunate result. Your Grace.

313
00:27:26.731 --> 00:27:28.731
Seasmoke has
fled Dragonstone.

314
00:27:28.732 --> 00:27:31.234
and Ser Steffon
was a valiant knight.

315
00:27:31.235 --> 00:27:32.943
Most regrettable.

316
00:27:32.944 --> 00:27:34.924
if. perhaps. foreseeable.

317
00:27:34.925 --> 00:27:36.905
I myself.
if you recall.

318
00:27:36.906 --> 00:27:38.950
was in favor of treating
with Lord Mooton

319
00:27:38.951 --> 00:27:40.117
to march
on Rook's Rest.

320
00:27:40.118 --> 00:27:42.641
A more
conventional approach.

321
00:27:42.642 --> 00:27:45.164
true. not
as sensational.

322
00:27:45.165 --> 00:27:47.584
And. uh. his...
his numbers were few.

323
00:27:47.585 --> 00:27:49.794
but we may
yet retake...

324
00:27:52.505 --> 00:27:55.717
It is my fault. I think.
that you have forgotten to fear me.

325
00:28:36.716 --> 00:28:39.219
It was worth the risk.
no matter the outcome.

326
00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:41.346
More good men killed?

327
00:28:41.930 --> 00:28:44.307
- That's my fault.
- Ser Steffon went willingly.

328
00:28:44.308 --> 00:28:46.225
It was
a reckless thought.

329
00:28:46.226 --> 00:28:47.956
That an ancient
Valyrian beast

330
00:28:47.957 --> 00:28:49.687
would suffer
a Darklyn to ride it.

331
00:28:49.688 --> 00:28:52.023
Surely he was
not the only possibility.

332
00:28:52.024 --> 00:28:53.315
Might there
not be others

333
00:28:53.316 --> 00:28:54.984
among the highborn
of the Seven Kingdoms?

334
00:28:54.985 --> 00:28:56.798
And who will be
so foolish as to try.

335
00:28:56.799 --> 00:28:58.613
after hearing what
befell Ser Steffon?

336
00:29:05.203 --> 00:29:06.788
I will
look again.

337
00:29:08.039 --> 00:29:11.001
But Darklyn had
the most likely claim.

338
00:29:11.002 --> 00:29:13.002
There is good news
to be had.

339
00:29:13.003 --> 00:29:15.714
The smallfolk
of King's Landing are listening.

340
00:29:15.715 --> 00:29:17.632
They were ready
enough to hear.

341
00:29:17.633 --> 00:29:19.550
The usurpers have
abandoned them.

342
00:29:19.551 --> 00:29:22.762
They are hungry.
and they need someone to blame.

343
00:29:24.222 --> 00:29:25.389
Will it
be enough?

344
00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:26.891
We have laid
the kindling only.

345
00:29:26.892 --> 00:29:28.497
Tonight we
will light it.

346
00:29:28.498 --> 00:29:30.102
and watch it
begin to flare.

347
00:29:30.103 --> 00:29:32.230
And when it does.
Aemond will put it down with force.

348
00:29:32.231 --> 00:29:33.898
That will make it
rise the hotter.

349
00:29:34.315 --> 00:29:36.171
He cannot destroy
his own city.

350
00:29:36.172 --> 00:29:38.027
Neither can they
overthrow him.

351
00:29:38.028 --> 00:29:41.281
Maybe not. but it is harder
to wage war abroad

352
00:29:41.282 --> 00:29:44.159
when you must also
keep peace at home.

353
00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:47.912
Then let us see
to our plan.

354
00:29:53.001 --> 00:29:55.003
If I may.
Your Grace...

355
00:29:56.421 --> 00:29:58.965
this becomes you.

356
00:30:16.149 --> 00:30:18.609
- That's the last one.
- Thank you.

357
00:30:18.610 --> 00:30:21.446
- What? They haven't run out. have they?
- Nothing.

358
00:30:22.322 --> 00:30:23.989
There ain't
nothing left.

359
00:30:23.990 --> 00:30:27.535
I've been waiting all day.
I'll take anything. Scraps?

360
00:30:37.295 --> 00:30:40.632
Got enough sheep for your dragons then.
but none for us.

361
00:30:40.633 --> 00:30:43.635
Where's our meat?
We want meat!

362
00:30:48.014 --> 00:30:50.161
<i>It seems. Your Grace.</i>

363
00:30:50.162 --> 00:30:52.310
<i>that the smallfolk
have become restless.</i>

364
00:30:52.311 --> 00:30:53.811
So?

365
00:30:53.812 --> 00:30:56.438
There is not
food enough in the city.

366
00:30:56.439 --> 00:30:59.275
Those with means
have bought more than their share.

367
00:30:59.276 --> 00:31:02.112
All the more reason
Ser Tyland must break the blockade.

368
00:31:02.113 --> 00:31:04.656
In the meantime.
the people are hungry.

369
00:31:04.657 --> 00:31:06.574
and their anger
is rising.

370
00:31:07.867 --> 00:31:09.703
The enemy without
may be fought with swords.

371
00:31:09.704 --> 00:31:12.184
The enemy within
is more insidious.

372
00:31:12.185 --> 00:31:14.666
Why is this anger
directed at us?

373
00:31:14.667 --> 00:31:15.834
It is Rhaenyra
the Pretender

374
00:31:15.835 --> 00:31:17.335
who ordered
the Gullet closed

375
00:31:17.336 --> 00:31:18.836
and left them
all to starve.

376
00:31:18.837 --> 00:31:20.839
They still look to you
to ensure their well-being.

377
00:31:22.340 --> 00:31:23.925
That is the burden
of authority.

378
00:31:25.051 --> 00:31:27.053
But you should not
go it alone.

379
00:31:28.513 --> 00:31:31.850
It does occur to me that Your Grace
has yet to name a Hand.

380
00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:34.977
Ser Criston. of course.
served your brother.

381
00:31:34.978 --> 00:31:37.355
but you need one
who may advance your cause...

382
00:31:37.939 --> 00:31:39.274
with shrewdness
and subtlety.

383
00:31:41.276 --> 00:31:43.111
Do you take me
for a fool?

384
00:31:46.698 --> 00:31:48.575
- On the contrary. my prince.
- I've little patience

385
00:31:48.576 --> 00:31:50.659
for the self-important.
Lord Larys.

386
00:31:50.660 --> 00:31:53.288
and even less for flatterers
and lickspittles.

387
00:31:54.622 --> 00:31:56.249
But you are.
as it happens. correct.

388
00:31:57.208 --> 00:31:58.793
Every king
needs a Hand.

389
00:32:00.628 --> 00:32:02.047
I'll make it
your responsibility.

390
00:32:04.549 --> 00:32:07.218
My prince. it is an honor
I'd never considered

391
00:32:07.219 --> 00:32:10.347
- for myself.
- No. not to serve as Hand. you toad.

392
00:32:10.348 --> 00:32:13.516
To fetch him.
Send word to Otto Hightower.

393
00:32:13.517 --> 00:32:15.225
My grandsire may
be overcautious.

394
00:32:15.226 --> 00:32:18.438
but his devotion
to his family has never been in doubt.

395
00:32:19.731 --> 00:32:21.399
Mm. you'll
see it done.

396
00:32:21.400 --> 00:32:23.067
Your Grace.

397
00:32:23.068 --> 00:32:25.110
You're late.

398
00:32:25.111 --> 00:32:28.009
I am happy to report
that His Grace the king

399
00:32:28.010 --> 00:32:30.909
has regained consciousness
this morning.

400
00:32:30.910 --> 00:32:32.576
if only
for a few moments.

401
00:32:32.577 --> 00:32:34.620
You said there was
little hope.

402
00:32:34.621 --> 00:32:36.748
He is stronger than I thought.

403
00:32:36.749 --> 00:32:39.125
This morning
his breath comes easier.

404
00:32:39.126 --> 00:32:42.253
He may yet live.
thank the gods.

405
00:32:42.254 --> 00:32:44.130
What happy news.

406
00:33:02.148 --> 00:33:03.441
I'll see my brother.

407
00:33:04.651 --> 00:33:05.860
Alone.

408
00:33:28.299 --> 00:33:29.801
What do you
remember?

409
00:33:35.306 --> 00:33:36.683
Nothing.

410
00:33:50.572 --> 00:33:52.574
You challenged
Meleys.

411
00:33:54.576 --> 00:33:56.202
It was foolish.

412
00:33:59.330 --> 00:34:02.334
I remember... nothing.

413
00:34:16.181 --> 00:34:20.185
- My prince?
- You're in the most capable hands. Your Grace.

414
00:34:28.026 --> 00:34:31.613
It seems my brother has a long recovery
ahead of him. Grand Maester.

415
00:34:34.074 --> 00:34:36.910
See that he is made
to rest comfortably.

416
00:34:42.207 --> 00:34:44.668
<i>And I've decided there is nothing</i>

417
00:34:44.669 --> 00:34:46.419
<i>to be gained
with fretfulness.</i>

418
00:34:47.212 --> 00:34:51.549
Not all of us. I suppose.
are called to great deeds.

419
00:34:53.551 --> 00:34:55.804
Some of us must serve
in smaller ways...

420
00:34:56.888 --> 00:35:00.058
even if they are not what we would
choose for ourselves.

421
00:35:01.101 --> 00:35:03.540
Meaning no offense. hm?

422
00:35:03.541 --> 00:35:05.980
None of this
is your fault.

423
00:35:08.421 --> 00:35:10.068
I want Mother.

424
00:35:11.444 --> 00:35:14.447
Yes... well...

425
00:35:15.740 --> 00:35:18.451
I know
it's difficult. but...

426
00:35:58.700 --> 00:36:01.160
I bring good news. Rhaena.

427
00:36:01.161 --> 00:36:03.558
Prince Reggio
has answered your letter.

428
00:36:03.559 --> 00:36:05.957
He'll be most pleased
to shelter Rhaenyra's

429
00:36:05.958 --> 00:36:08.043
youngest sons
in Pentos.

430
00:36:09.127 --> 00:36:11.296
And their
half-sister.

431
00:36:15.216 --> 00:36:17.218
Thought you'd
be happy.

432
00:36:18.803 --> 00:36:20.846
Or at least
less morose.

433
00:36:20.847 --> 00:36:24.142
You hate it here.

434
00:36:26.644 --> 00:36:28.646
You misled me. my lady.

435
00:36:30.982 --> 00:36:32.192
I did what?

436
00:36:34.319 --> 00:36:37.155
There is a large
dragon in the Vale.

437
00:36:41.701 --> 00:36:44.746
Rumor of it began shortly
after the war.

438
00:36:45.246 --> 00:36:48.041
Ranging more broadly
for food...

439
00:36:48.042 --> 00:36:50.085
my maesters
surmise.

440
00:36:54.214 --> 00:36:59.886
It is large and formidable.
but alas. wild.

441
00:37:01.346 --> 00:37:02.681
Alas.

442
00:37:05.016 --> 00:37:07.352
A merchant cog.
the <i>Gay Abandon.</i>

443
00:37:07.353 --> 00:37:09.187
will take you to Pentos.

444
00:37:11.731 --> 00:37:14.150
I'll send six good men
to protect you on the crossing.

445
00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:28.248
You know you're
not fooling anyone.

446
00:37:30.375 --> 00:37:33.878
Lord Corlys has chosen
to raise you up

447
00:37:33.879 --> 00:37:35.547
to serve alongside him

448
00:37:36.214 --> 00:37:39.843
and yet.
you still continue this subterfuge.

449
00:37:40.385 --> 00:37:42.512
Don't want my men
to get the wrong idea.

450
00:37:42.513 --> 00:37:43.722
About what?

451
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:50.374
You're just like him.

452
00:37:50.375 --> 00:37:52.730
Oh. you make an art
of provoking me.

453
00:37:52.731 --> 00:37:54.941
You saved his life. brother.

454
00:37:54.942 --> 00:37:57.152
Do you never
think about what could be ours?

455
00:37:58.069 --> 00:37:59.904
Or yours. anyway.

456
00:38:00.989 --> 00:38:04.576
The riches...
servants...

457
00:38:05.744 --> 00:38:07.036
the Driftwood Throne.

458
00:38:07.037 --> 00:38:08.412
We spent the whole
of our lives

459
00:38:08.413 --> 00:38:11.624
in the shadow
of the Sea Snake's great castle.

460
00:38:11.625 --> 00:38:13.876
I do not wish
to dwell in it any longer.

461
00:38:13.877 --> 00:38:17.130
Hm. and so you belittle
your great opportunity.

462
00:38:17.922 --> 00:38:21.926
While me
he ignores...

463
00:38:22.677 --> 00:38:24.596
as he always has.

464
00:38:26.765 --> 00:38:29.600
The Sea Snake
would sooner have High Tide

465
00:38:29.601 --> 00:38:32.437
claimed by the sea
than call us his sons.

466
00:38:34.272 --> 00:38:37.942
Stop wasting your life waiting
for something that'll never come.

467
00:39:03.134 --> 00:39:05.156
It was
a bold attempt.

468
00:39:05.157 --> 00:39:07.180
I admire
you for it.

469
00:39:11.142 --> 00:39:13.770
They say you struck
Lord Bartimos today

470
00:39:14.354 --> 00:39:16.356
in view of the staff
and guard.

471
00:39:17.691 --> 00:39:19.693
The household
is abuzz with it.

472
00:39:21.486 --> 00:39:24.322
He's lucky I did not
have his tongue.

473
00:39:24.323 --> 00:39:27.534
And what did he say
that was so

474
00:39:27.535 --> 00:39:29.202
deserving?

475
00:39:32.080 --> 00:39:34.499
I have tired
of being protected...

476
00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:36.167
Jace.

477
00:39:39.504 --> 00:39:41.840
I bring to mind
too much their mothers

478
00:39:41.841 --> 00:39:43.508
or their daughters.

479
00:39:44.426 --> 00:39:46.719
They must see
in me a ruler.

480
00:39:46.720 --> 00:39:49.139
And the symbols of authority
are not jewels and gowns.

481
00:39:49.140 --> 00:39:50.682
but the shield
and the sword.

482
00:39:50.683 --> 00:39:53.642
My ruler is
my mother.

483
00:39:53.643 --> 00:39:56.062
And I do not wish
it otherwise.

484
00:39:58.773 --> 00:40:00.649
Will you lead us
to war yourself?

485
00:40:00.650 --> 00:40:02.192
Well. for a certainty
I cannot remain here.

486
00:40:02.193 --> 00:40:04.738
pacing the floors. waiting for defeat
and despair to visit me.

487
00:40:04.739 --> 00:40:07.219
- Oh. don't be ridiculous.
- I'm doing all I can.

488
00:40:07.220 --> 00:40:09.356
I have directed
Lord Mooton to march on Rook's Rest.

489
00:40:09.357 --> 00:40:11.494
and sent another raven
to the Vale to persuade...

490
00:40:11.495 --> 00:40:13.955
We may marshal
the strength of the Vale.

491
00:40:13.956 --> 00:40:16.416
Maidenpool. and all
our allies besides.

492
00:40:16.916 --> 00:40:20.128
We will still never match
the strength of the Green armies.

493
00:40:21.713 --> 00:40:24.048
We need Daemon
and his dragon.

494
00:40:24.049 --> 00:40:26.383
May I be free
for even one hour

495
00:40:26.384 --> 00:40:28.678
of the constant refrain of Daemon.
Daemon. Daemon...

496
00:40:28.679 --> 00:40:30.096
Your Grace.

497
00:40:30.972 --> 00:40:32.599
The lady Mysaria.

498
00:40:34.601 --> 00:40:37.812
My queen.
our gift is sent.

499
00:40:41.566 --> 00:40:42.984
What gift?

500
00:40:44.235 --> 00:40:46.613
Let us hope for clouds over
the Blackwater tonight.

501
00:43:08.213 --> 00:43:09.714
You said he'd improved.

502
00:43:11.883 --> 00:43:15.428
His Grace sleeps nine hours
of every 10...

503
00:43:16.096 --> 00:43:20.058
but he did open his eyes and speak.
however briefly.

504
00:43:20.059 --> 00:43:22.560
His mending may be
long and painful.

505
00:43:22.561 --> 00:43:24.561
but it is
my sincere hope

506
00:43:24.562 --> 00:43:26.897
that His Grace
will be spared.

507
00:43:26.898 --> 00:43:29.234
And what will he
be if he lives?

508
00:43:38.618 --> 00:43:42.080
My letters
to my father...

509
00:43:44.082 --> 00:43:49.254
I have sent ravens. again.
to Highgarden and to Oldtown.

510
00:43:49.255 --> 00:43:52.590
And now. to all
the great houses in the Reach.

511
00:43:52.591 --> 00:43:54.926
There has been no word
from Ser Otto.

512
00:43:54.927 --> 00:43:56.428
as of yet.

513
00:44:01.933 --> 00:44:05.102
There is war in the Reach now.
Your Grace.

514
00:44:05.103 --> 00:44:09.065
House Beesbury has raised arms against
the Hightower host.

515
00:44:09.066 --> 00:44:12.610
Retribution for
their lord's demise.

516
00:44:40.513 --> 00:44:42.140
I'm sorry.

517
00:44:43.641 --> 00:44:45.246
I'm sorry.

518
00:45:24.849 --> 00:45:26.559
Sister.

519
00:45:26.560 --> 00:45:27.852
Gwayne.

520
00:45:29.437 --> 00:45:31.439
'Tis well that
I found you.

521
00:45:32.357 --> 00:45:34.359
I wish to give you
my blessing.

522
00:45:34.943 --> 00:45:36.860
Well...

523
00:45:36.861 --> 00:45:39.531
my thanks
to the queen dowager.

524
00:45:45.078 --> 00:45:47.413
I wondered if you've
heard from father?

525
00:45:47.414 --> 00:45:49.749
I've sent ravens
to Highgarden and Oldtown.

526
00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:51.668
but have
had no reply.

527
00:45:51.669 --> 00:45:53.711
I've heard nothing

528
00:45:53.712 --> 00:45:55.797
but neither have
I sent any message.

529
00:45:56.214 --> 00:45:58.341
If he wrote letters.
it would be to you.

530
00:45:58.342 --> 00:46:00.427
You were always
his favorite.

531
00:46:00.885 --> 00:46:02.595
Strange there
has been no word.

532
00:46:03.263 --> 00:46:06.390
Otto Hightower is
ever-resourceful.

533
00:46:06.391 --> 00:46:08.935
He will send news
when there is news to send.

534
00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:14.231
I often wonder what
life could've been

535
00:46:14.232 --> 00:46:16.234
if he had brought
you to court instead.

536
00:46:18.653 --> 00:46:20.279
I'm the eldest son.

537
00:46:20.280 --> 00:46:22.364
It was right
that I was raised at Oldtown.

538
00:46:22.365 --> 00:46:23.908
But you were eight years of age
and motherless.

539
00:46:23.909 --> 00:46:25.242
It must've
been difficult.

540
00:46:25.243 --> 00:46:27.912
You get on with it.
don't you?

541
00:46:29.497 --> 00:46:31.499
When there
isn't any choice.

542
00:46:34.919 --> 00:46:36.338
My son. Daeron...

543
00:46:39.632 --> 00:46:41.259
what's he like?

544
00:46:41.843 --> 00:46:45.180
- Does he not write to you?
- Less and less these days.

545
00:46:47.807 --> 00:46:49.434
Ten-and-six now.

546
00:46:50.977 --> 00:46:53.980
Letters. perhaps.
hold less of his interest.

547
00:46:58.485 --> 00:47:00.487
He's stalwart.

548
00:47:01.363 --> 00:47:02.405
Clever.

549
00:47:02.822 --> 00:47:05.825
As adept with his lute
as he is with his sword.

550
00:47:07.035 --> 00:47:08.787
And a feature
in the fancies of many

551
00:47:08.788 --> 00:47:11.039
a young lady.
I'll wager.

552
00:47:15.210 --> 00:47:16.628
He's kind.

553
00:47:20.507 --> 00:47:22.133
That's good.

554
00:47:24.177 --> 00:47:28.431
- Kindness is a quality I've found lacking in his brothers.
- Mm.

555
00:47:28.807 --> 00:47:31.059
You did well
to send him to ward.

556
00:47:31.643 --> 00:47:33.415
Yes. it seems
the Red Keep.

557
00:47:33.416 --> 00:47:35.187
for all its
privileges.

558
00:47:35.188 --> 00:47:38.942
may. in fact. be a less
than salubrious environment

559
00:47:38.943 --> 00:47:40.819
for the forming
of young men.

560
00:47:42.153 --> 00:47:44.989
Was it the court
or was it their mother?

561
00:47:47.158 --> 00:47:49.160
I'm sure you
did your best.

562
00:47:55.041 --> 00:47:57.669
I must join
Ser Criston.

563
00:47:58.378 --> 00:48:01.296
Wish us luck. sister.

564
00:48:01.297 --> 00:48:03.633
I shall pray to the Warrior
for your safe return.

565
00:48:06.594 --> 00:48:07.846
Mm...

566
00:48:09.055 --> 00:48:10.265
Farewell.

567
00:48:52.307 --> 00:48:53.725
Your Grace.

568
00:48:56.728 --> 00:48:58.563
This one stopped singing.

569
00:48:59.731 --> 00:49:01.733
Isn't that strange?

570
00:49:02.484 --> 00:49:06.112
I thought
we might light a candle.

571
00:49:07.280 --> 00:49:08.740
For Aegon...

572
00:49:10.116 --> 00:49:12.118
and all our
lost souls.

573
00:49:43.441 --> 00:49:45.151
You. where'd you
get that food?!

574
00:49:45.152 --> 00:49:46.735
- Rhaenyra's ships.
- Ships?

575
00:49:46.736 --> 00:49:48.154
They came ashore
in the middle of the night

576
00:49:48.155 --> 00:49:49.822
with gifts
from the queen.

577
00:49:49.823 --> 00:49:51.491
She thinks of us.
even now!

578
00:50:06.131 --> 00:50:07.340
Give me that!

579
00:50:08.633 --> 00:50:11.469
Give it to me!

580
00:50:16.307 --> 00:50:18.268
Get out of the way!

581
00:50:37.454 --> 00:50:41.207
Your Graces...
we must leave. now.

582
00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:48.923
Get the queens
to the wheelhouse!

583
00:50:52.844 --> 00:50:55.347
Mind your flanks.
Protect your corners.

584
00:50:57.265 --> 00:51:00.226
Keep moving.
This way. Your Grace.

585
00:51:02.437 --> 00:51:04.229
'Tis the Queen
of Fishes!

586
00:51:06.192 --> 00:51:07.900
Keep moving!

587
00:51:07.901 --> 00:51:10.298
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

588
00:51:10.299 --> 00:51:12.697
Get to the wheelhouse!

589
00:51:12.698 --> 00:51:14.032
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

590
00:51:14.033 --> 00:51:15.867
Helaena!

591
00:51:15.868 --> 00:51:17.285
Your Grace!

592
00:51:18.703 --> 00:51:20.705
- My queen!
- Get off!

593
00:51:20.706 --> 00:51:23.540
No! No!

594
00:51:23.541 --> 00:51:25.381
Sheathe your swords!

595
00:51:26.961 --> 00:51:28.545
Sheathe your swords!

596
00:51:30.883 --> 00:51:32.425
You heard the queen!

597
00:51:32.426 --> 00:51:34.094
Sheathe those swords!

598
00:51:42.102 --> 00:51:44.396
No!

599
00:51:45.397 --> 00:51:47.564
- Get back!
- Go. Helaena. go!

600
00:51:47.565 --> 00:51:49.734
Out of my way!
Out of my way!

601
00:51:56.324 --> 00:51:58.326
Estermont!

602
00:51:59.452 --> 00:52:02.789
My Queens!
This way. inside!

603
00:52:15.260 --> 00:52:18.430
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

604
00:52:20.140 --> 00:52:22.809
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

605
00:52:24.978 --> 00:52:26.646
Run them down if you must.

606
00:52:28.440 --> 00:52:30.816
Ride! Ride!

607
00:53:07.729 --> 00:53:09.480
No more.

608
00:53:09.481 --> 00:53:11.399
My lord. Only...

609
00:53:11.400 --> 00:53:13.317
...the Grand Maester
instructed me to.

610
00:53:13.318 --> 00:53:15.862
The king will be most eager
for his draught.

611
00:53:15.863 --> 00:53:17.154
in an hour.

612
00:53:29.834 --> 00:53:32.503
The drink takes
the pain away.

613
00:53:32.504 --> 00:53:35.465
but it dulls your mind.

614
00:53:35.466 --> 00:53:36.674
Oh. take heart.
Your Grace.

615
00:53:36.675 --> 00:53:38.677
you've already written
yourself into legend.

616
00:53:38.678 --> 00:53:40.887
You survived
dragonfire.

617
00:53:43.890 --> 00:53:45.850
But I'm afraid you
will never be whole.

618
00:53:47.352 --> 00:53:49.938
{\an8}Orwyle has exhausted
his abilities.

619
00:53:50.897 --> 00:53:52.524
{\an8}He's bound
your leg...

620
00:53:54.526 --> 00:53:56.736
{\an8}but you will
never run again.

621
00:53:58.239 --> 00:54:00.155
Your mind...

622
00:54:00.156 --> 00:54:02.178
is all that
remains to you.

623
00:54:02.179 --> 00:54:04.202
I do not
say that gladly.

624
00:54:08.039 --> 00:54:10.040
I came screaming
into the world

625
00:54:10.041 --> 00:54:13.086
in the bowels of one
of Harren's great towers.

626
00:54:15.046 --> 00:54:18.049
My lungs were strong.
but my foot

627
00:54:18.050 --> 00:54:20.218
so twisted that...

628
00:54:21.302 --> 00:54:24.305
my father named
it sorcery.

629
00:54:25.640 --> 00:54:28.475
Accusing a member
of our household

630
00:54:28.476 --> 00:54:31.312
of casting...
maligned spells.

631
00:54:34.065 --> 00:54:35.483
{\an8}Well.

632
00:54:36.317 --> 00:54:38.527
{\an8}People will
pity you

633
00:54:38.528 --> 00:54:40.905
{\an8}either behind
your back...

634
00:54:40.906 --> 00:54:42.741
{\an8}or in your
presence.

635
00:54:44.576 --> 00:54:46.578
And they will stare...

636
00:54:48.747 --> 00:54:50.749
at you. at you...

637
00:54:53.418 --> 00:54:54.669
or turn away.

638
00:54:58.465 --> 00:55:00.925
And they will
underestimate you.

639
00:55:02.927 --> 00:55:04.971
And this will be
your advantage.

640
00:55:04.972 --> 00:55:07.265
No. n... No.

641
00:55:13.980 --> 00:55:16.503
Your brother rules
in your place now.

642
00:55:16.504 --> 00:55:19.027
which means that
your life is in danger.

643
00:55:21.029 --> 00:55:23.281
But I think
you know that.

644
00:55:27.827 --> 00:55:29.287
Help me.

645
00:56:15.041 --> 00:56:16.251
Brother.

646
00:56:18.878 --> 00:56:20.880
Daemon. she's gone.

647
00:56:34.019 --> 00:56:35.687
I'm sorry.

648
00:56:41.693 --> 00:56:43.528
You needed me.

649
00:56:45.864 --> 00:56:47.699
I'm here now.

650
00:56:56.958 --> 00:56:58.626
I'm here now.

651
00:57:04.090 --> 00:57:05.717
Your Grace.

652
00:57:08.470 --> 00:57:12.307
Sorrowful news
from Riverrun. my king.

653
00:57:13.224 --> 00:57:15.310
Lord Grover is dead.

654
00:57:17.395 --> 00:57:20.899
Uhh... the old man.

655
00:57:20.900 --> 00:57:21.900
Indeed.

656
00:57:22.734 --> 00:57:27.113
Young Oscar Tully is now Lord Paramount
of the Riverlands.

657
00:57:29.741 --> 00:57:32.243
What was the manner
of Lord Grover's passing?

658
00:57:32.244 --> 00:57:34.746
- Well. he'd been ill. of course.
- Mm-hmm.

659
00:57:35.580 --> 00:57:38.082
Riverrun's
maesters...

660
00:57:38.083 --> 00:57:40.334
have been
at their wits' end.

661
00:57:40.335 --> 00:57:43.045
Our own healer.
Alys Rivers.

662
00:57:43.046 --> 00:57:45.757
volunteered her
renowned skills.

663
00:57:45.758 --> 00:57:47.634
She plied
her craft. but...

664
00:57:49.761 --> 00:57:51.763
there was naught
more to be done.

665
00:58:29.718 --> 00:58:31.573
Hey. look!

666
00:58:34.024 --> 00:58:36.474
Get inside! Hurry!

667
01:00:09.734 --> 01:00:13.029
Your banners were carried
from the ship into the city.

668
01:00:13.030 --> 01:00:15.198
They went as far
as the gates of the Red Keep

669
01:00:15.199 --> 01:00:16.532
before they
were turned away.

670
01:00:16.533 --> 01:00:18.742
It is. as we hoped.
a warning to the usurpers

671
01:00:18.743 --> 01:00:21.788
that you have strength
beyond what they accredited.

672
01:00:23.915 --> 01:00:25.750
I thought
you'd be pleased.

673
01:00:27.585 --> 01:00:29.587
I do not think
I can win this war.

674
01:00:31.923 --> 01:00:33.382
I think you
are tired.

675
01:00:33.383 --> 01:00:36.261
My own son questions
my capabilities.

676
01:00:38.680 --> 01:00:40.682
He thinks I need
Daemon at my side.

677
01:00:43.101 --> 01:00:47.689
- And Daemon himself.
- He has ever done what suits Daemon.

678
01:00:52.193 --> 01:00:54.446
He was everything
I wanted to be.

679
01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:56.948
Carefree.

680
01:00:57.949 --> 01:00:59.367
And dangerous.

681
01:01:00.994 --> 01:01:02.203
A man.

682
01:01:03.538 --> 01:01:05.477
And I was what
he wanted.

683
01:01:05.478 --> 01:01:07.469
Cherished by
my father.

684
01:01:07.470 --> 01:01:09.591
and made
my father's heir.

685
01:01:09.592 --> 01:01:11.713
We were halves
of a whole.

686
01:01:14.507 --> 01:01:16.509
He's never been at peace.

687
01:01:18.636 --> 01:01:19.971
He wished to possess me.

688
01:01:19.972 --> 01:01:22.139
but not to be
possessed

689
01:01:22.140 --> 01:01:24.329
and to see me
take hold. finally.

690
01:01:24.330 --> 01:01:26.519
of what he always
believed to be his.

691
01:01:28.980 --> 01:01:30.690
I fear what
he may now do.

692
01:01:37.405 --> 01:01:39.449
I fear he may have
turned against me.

693
01:01:39.450 --> 01:01:41.847
It is more his way
to disappear.

694
01:01:41.848 --> 01:01:44.245
In either case.
I have lost him...

695
01:01:45.163 --> 01:01:47.164
and Caraxes with him.

696
01:01:47.165 --> 01:01:49.333
Rhaenys
and her dragon are dead.

697
01:01:49.334 --> 01:01:51.523
I have Syrax
and two young beasts.

698
01:01:51.524 --> 01:01:53.712
We cannot take
on Vhagar alone.

699
01:01:53.713 --> 01:01:57.926
- And I have no army.
- You have the Velaryon fleet and the men who fight in it.

700
01:01:59.552 --> 01:02:01.012
It's not enough.

701
01:02:02.222 --> 01:02:04.849
And even if we
somehow prevailed.

702
01:02:04.850 --> 01:02:06.350
how will I rule
a kingdom

703
01:02:06.351 --> 01:02:07.852
when my own
son doubts me?

704
01:02:08.853 --> 01:02:09.854
You have me.

705
01:02:12.691 --> 01:02:16.111
You have my thanks...
Truly.

706
01:02:28.748 --> 01:02:30.959
It was my father.

707
01:02:36.548 --> 01:02:38.341
I was still a child.

708
01:02:38.883 --> 01:02:42.887
He...
had his pleasure with me.

709
01:02:43.555 --> 01:02:45.389
And when.
after many months of this.

710
01:02:45.390 --> 01:02:50.061
it became evident
that his seed had taken root.

711
01:02:57.777 --> 01:02:59.988
There is a scar
here as well.

712
01:03:01.656 --> 01:03:03.908
I cannot
bear children.

713
01:03:05.744 --> 01:03:07.412
He left me
for dead...

714
01:03:08.913 --> 01:03:10.081
but I lived.

715
01:03:10.623 --> 01:03:14.210
- I'm so sorry.
- Swore to myself I would never trust another.

716
01:03:14.211 --> 01:03:18.423
And... that oath
has stood me well.

717
01:03:18.424 --> 01:03:20.758
This world is
cold and cruel.

718
01:03:20.759 --> 01:03:24.721
and there are
few in it who are steadfast.

719
01:03:24.722 --> 01:03:28.725
You. I think.
are steadfast.

720
01:03:29.434 --> 01:03:33.271
You have seen me as worthy.
as an equal. even.

721
01:03:34.272 --> 01:03:36.691
Because of that.
I will serve you.

722
01:03:37.275 --> 01:03:40.111
I believe you are
meant to be queen.

723
01:04:51.516 --> 01:04:54.477
Begging your pardon.
Your Grace.

724
01:04:55.186 --> 01:04:58.982
The dragon Seasmoke
has been sighted flying over Spicetown.

725
01:04:58.983 --> 01:05:00.733
Yes. he does that.

726
01:05:00.734 --> 01:05:02.402
From what
we have heard...

727
01:05:02.944 --> 01:05:04.362
he has a rider.

728
01:05:04.779 --> 01:05:08.033
- Who?
- Impossible to tell from the ground.

729
01:05:08.742 --> 01:05:11.286
- The Greens?
- I don't know who else it could be.

730
01:05:11.703 --> 01:05:13.246
Shall I summon
your counsel?

731
01:05:34.726 --> 01:05:36.227
Mother!
